00:00:02.719 --> 00:00:07.080
turned into charts. You can keep them as reports too. but before we can

00:00:07.080 --> 00:00:10.140
turn it into a chart, we have to change the report type. because right

00:00:10.140 --> 00:00:13.260
now, if you see next to the preview we're set to the tabular format.

00:00:13.260 --> 00:00:13.520
&gt;&gt; huh.

00:00:13.520 --> 00:00:15.750
&gt;&gt; And the tabular format is the simplest type

00:00:15.750 --> 00:00:17.320
of report, which is what we're looking at right now.

00:00:17.320 --> 00:00:17.510
&gt;&gt; huh.

00:00:17.510 --> 00:00:19.580
&gt;&gt; Just simple like a spreadsheet. But

00:00:19.580 --> 00:00:21.240
you can't actually turn that into a dashboard.

00:00:21.240 --> 00:00:21.610
&gt;&gt; Okay.

00:00:21.610 --> 00:00:23.610
&gt;&gt; So, if we click the other report types.

00:00:23.610 --> 00:00:24.410
&gt;&gt; Summary

00:00:24.410 --> 00:00:25.480
&gt;&gt; Summary, which is

00:00:25.480 --> 00:00:28.800
really similar to tabular, but it just adds a little grouping

00:00:28.800 --> 00:00:31.910
for you to be able to more granularly categorize the data.

00:00:31.910 --> 00:00:33.340
&gt;&gt; Can I click it and see what you mean?

00:00:33.340 --> 00:00:36.730
&gt;&gt; Yeah. 'Kay, so what do you mean by grouping? Like, what could I group on?

00:00:36.730 --> 00:00:40.340
